{"abstract":[{"text":"Working with PMTiles","type":"text"}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"title":"PMTiles","role":"article","roleHeading":"Article"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Starting MapLibre iOS 6.10.0, using "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/docs.protomaps.com\/pmtiles\/","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" as a data source is supported. You can prefix your vector tile source with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pmtiles:\/\/"},{"type":"text","text":" to load a PMTiles file. The rest of the URL continue with be "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"https:\/\/"},{"type":"text","text":" to load a remote PMTiles file, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"asset:\/\/"},{"type":"text","text":" to load an asset or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"file:\/\/"},{"type":"text","text":" to load a local PMTiles file."}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"PMTiles sources do not currently support offline pack downloads."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Oliver Wipfli has made a style available that combines a "},{"identifier":"","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" basemap togehter with Foursquare’s POI dataset. It is available in the "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/wipfli\/foursquare-os-places-pmtiles","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" repository on GitHub. The style to use is"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["https:\/\/raw.githubusercontent.com\/wipfli\/foursquare-os-places-pmtiles\/refs\/heads\/main\/style.json"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The neat thing about this style is that it only uses PMTiles vector sources. PMTiles can be hosted with a relatively simple file server (or file hosting service) instead of a more complex specialized tile server."}]},{"t